**Privacy Policy for Carnival VR by InfinityRealm Studios**

**Last Updated: September 14, 2023**

**Introduction**

InfinityRealm Studios ("we," "us," "our") is committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your personal information when you use our virtual reality (VR) application called Carnival VR (the "App"). By using the App, you consent to the practices described in this Privacy Policy.

**1. Information We Collect**

a. **Information You Provide:** We may collect information that you voluntarily provide when you use the App, such as your name, email address, and any other information you choose to share with us when you contact our support team or participate in surveys or feedback requests.

b. **Device Information:** We may collect information about your VR device, including its type, model, operating system, and unique device identifiers.

c. **Usage Information:** We may collect information about how you use the App, including your interactions, preferences, and activities within the App.

**2. How We Use Your Information**

We use the information we collect for the following purposes:

a. **To Provide and Improve the App:** We use your information to provide, maintain, and improve the App, including enhancing user experiences and adding new features.

b. **Communication:** We may use your contact information to send you updates, newsletters, and promotional materials related to Carnival VR. You can opt-out of receiving these communications at any time.

c. **Customer Support:** We use your information to respond to your inquiries and provide customer support.

d. **Analytics:** We use data analytics to better understand how users interact with the App and to improve its performance and content.

e. **Legal Compliance:** We may use your information to comply with applicable laws and regulations, and to protect our rights and the rights of other users.

**3. Sharing Your Information**

We may share your information with third parties under the following circumstances:

a. **Service Providers:** We may share your information with third-party service providers who assist us in providing the App, such as hosting services, analytics providers, and customer support services.

b. **Legal Requirements:** We may disclose your information if required by law, regulation, or legal process.

c. **Business Transfers:** If we are involved in a merger, acquisition, or sale of all or a portion of our assets, your information may be transferred as part of that transaction.

**4. Data Security**

We take reasonable measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction. However, no data transmission or storage system can be guaranteed to be 100% secure, so we cannot ensure or warrant the security of any information you transmit to us.

**5. Your Choices**

You can access, update, or delete your personal information by contacting us at [contact email]. You can also opt-out of receiving promotional emails from us by following the instructions provided in those emails.

**6. Children's Privacy**

The App is not intended for use by children under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe we have collected personal information from a child under 13, please contact us, and we will take steps to remove such information.

**7. Changes to this Privacy Policy**

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. We will notify you of any material changes by posting the updated Privacy Policy on our website or within the App.

**8. Contact Us**

If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or your personal information, please contact us at rajrjgohil@gmail.com.

Thank you for using Carnival VR by InfinityRealm Studios. Your privacy is important to us, and we are committed to protecting it.
